metadata.name: WTBS Logo with Fractals #243
metadata.description:
Hard to believe we are going into month 3 of making the podcast! In February we further honed our sound thanks to new microphones and editing, and released our first two artist interview episodes w/ abstractment and MJLindow. Lots more interviews to come!

Thank you to everyone who takes the time to write us kind messages of support. Extra thanks to everyone who helps to grow the show by sharing/retweeting. Extra extra thanks to everyone who supports us through donations and/or collecting our NFT releases.

This project is coded in p5.js with help from abstractment (master of formatting). It is quite a bit different from the first... hopefully you will enjoy the added complexity and variations. There were quite a few discoveries and happy accidents along the way to make it possible. If you are new to coding or otherwise interested in learning, please feel free to browse the code. Effort has been made to explain, as best as possible, how everything works with comments... although this will assume a bit more knowledge than the last.

metadata.name: Action Fields #397
metadata.description:
A generative painting based on abstract expressionism and the action paintings of Jackson Pollock.

Several different flow fields are used to create paths which are then painted in one of four different styles (pastel, paint, Pollock, black+gold). Additional features affect the background, path length + angles, level of detail, and mess (drips and splats). 

NOTES: 
- Some variations of the Pollock style may appear slightly different between browsers, but will render consistently in the same browser. 
- On slower devices, it may take some time to being drawing due to the background rendering.
- If you get a browser warning that the page is taking a long time, press continue.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ‚Äôs‚Äô to save a screenshot. Image size is 1200x928px
Press ‚Äôp‚Äô to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 5,000 px. The ideal higher resolution is 2,000px.

metadata.name: chor√©graphie #220
metadata.description:
‚Ä¶ divided in two,
like the parent in sound and motion.
yet not exactly the same, I get ‚Ä¶


chor√©graphie explores the algorithmic characteristics of recursion in audiovisual form.

The algorithm performs a recursive split. At each split stage, space is divided into four different sized quadrants. Each split stage will eventually spawn an oscillator or a synthesizer representing the current properties of recursion in sound. The process is recursively repeated until a maximum recursion depth is reached or an early return condition is met.
Additionally, an initial motion funnction is randomly selected and propageted through the recursion, so that each recursive split stage with move depending on it‚Äôs split properties in combination with time.

Click into the piece to start the audio. Each piece can be seeded with a new initial configuration by pressing the ‚Äòs‚Äô key.
